715138f-a.title: Manhattan: 116th Street (West) - 5th Avenue
715138f-a.text:
West 116th Street, west from (No. 11-13) but not including Fifth Ave.,
showing W.P.A. employees engaged in removing street car tracks. The
building with the flag is P.S. No. 184 and bears No. A1 West 116th Street.
It occupies the site between Nos. 19-21 and 35. The Jewel Theatre
(motion picture) is No. 11-13 and is slightly west of the N.W. corner of
Fifth Ave.
January 4, 1937.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Proiect.
